+    '',
+    'Overall conclusion: objective_response in this cohort is not explained by one feature alone. Several feature columns show reproducible main-effect differences in absolute response probability, and several feature pairs show clinically meaningful heterogeneity on the same natural probability scale. The most persuasive findings are the associations and interactions that remain significant after false-discovery adjustment and have nontrivial absolute risk differences; nominal-only or near-zero effects in the transcript should be treated as weak or refuted hypotheses.',
+    '',
+    'Caveats: feature labels are de-identified opaque variables, so the results describe statistical treatment-biomarker-outcome structure but cannot be clinically interpreted as named biomarkers without a separate data dictionary. All tests are observational associations, not causal estimates.',
+  ].join('\n');
+
+  fs.writeFileSync('transcript.json', `${JSON.stringify(transcript, null, 2)}\n`, 'utf8');
+  fs.writeFileSync('analysis_summary.txt', `${summary}\n`, 'utf8');
+
+  console.log(`Read ${numRows} rows and ${features.length} features from ${DATASET}.`);
+  console.log(`Overall objective_response rate: ${pct(responseRate)}`);
+  console.log('Top main effects:');
+  console.log(topMainLines.join('\n'));
+  console.log('Top pairwise interactions:');
+  console.log(topInteractionLines.join('\n'));
+}
+
+main();

